All tarsi pale (
<figureCitation box="[366,424,1453,1474]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1971,1993]" captionTargetBox="[220,1377,215,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[204,1379,193,1942]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Merodon nanus, hind leg, lateral view; A. male; B. female. Tarsi of the hind leg of female, dorsal view; C. M. telmateia; D. M. nanus. Dotted areas indicate darkly pigmented cuticle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245531/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="452">
