<figureCitation box="[826,885,1512,1533]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1971,1993]" captionTargetBox="[220,1377,215,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[204,1379,193,1942]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Merodon nanus, hind leg, lateral view; A. male; B. female. Tarsi of the hind leg of female, dorsal view; C. M. telmateia; D. M. nanus. Dotted areas indicate darkly pigmented cuticle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245531/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="452">
Fig. 
<number box="[872,885,1512,1533]" pageId="13" pageNumber="452" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
D). Male genitalia: hypandrium with rounded or slightly pointed apex (
<figureCitation box="[361,427,1541,1562]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1656,1678]" captionTargetBox="[179,1429,250,1577]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[167,1437,229,1592]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Male genitalia. A – C. Merodon nanus; D. M. rasicus sp. n. A. Epandrium, lateral view; B. hypandrium, lateral view; C – D. distal end of the aedeagus, ventral view; ps – posterior surstyle lobe; c – cercus; ih – inner processes of the hypandrium; ab – aedeagal box; n – notch on theca to which is attached the aedeagal apodeme; e – ejaculatory apodeme." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245532/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="452">
Figs. 
<number box="[415,427,1541,1562]" pageId="13" pageNumber="452" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
B, 
<number box="[455,468,1541,1562]" pageId="13" pageNumber="452" value="6.0">6</number>
B, 
<number box="[495,507,1541,1562]" pageId="13" pageNumber="452" value="8.0">8</number>
C, 
<number box="[535,547,1541,1562]" pageId="13" pageNumber="452" value="9.0">9</number>
