<number box="[1060,1118,1571,1592]" pageId="13" pageNumber="452" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2 to 3</number>
times shorter than the length of hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[354,420,1600,1621]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1971,1993]" captionTargetBox="[220,1377,215,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[204,1379,193,1942]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Merodon nanus, hind leg, lateral view; A. male; B. female. Tarsi of the hind leg of female, dorsal view; C. M. telmateia; D. M. nanus. Dotted areas indicate darkly pigmented cuticle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245531/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="452">
