</figureCitation>
B, 
<number box="[1157,1170,1600,1621]" pageId="13" pageNumber="452" value="9.0">9</number>
B); ventral margin of posterior lobe of surstylus moderately convex or almost straight (
<figureCitation box="[800,866,1629,1650]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1656,1678]" captionTargetBox="[179,1429,250,1577]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[167,1437,229,1592]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Male genitalia. A – C. Merodon nanus; D. M. rasicus sp. n. A. Epandrium, lateral view; B. hypandrium, lateral view; C – D. distal end of the aedeagus, ventral view; ps – posterior surstyle lobe; c – cercus; ih – inner processes of the hypandrium; ab – aedeagal box; n – notch on theca to which is attached the aedeagal apodeme; e – ejaculatory apodeme." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245532/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="452">
Figs. 
<number box="[854,866,1629,1650]" pageId="13" pageNumber="452" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number box="[895,907,1629,1650]" pageId="13" pageNumber="452" value="9.0">9</number>
A)....................................... 
<number box="[1423,1435,1629,1650]" pageId="13" pageNumber="452" value="4.0">4</number>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1453,2032]" pageId="13" pageNumber="452">
<keyLead pageId="13" pageNumber="452">
- 
<collectingCountry box="[225,273,1659,1680]" name="India" pageId="13" pageNumber="452">Hind</collectingCountry>
