<number box="[1360,1373,1688,1709]" pageId="13" pageNumber="452" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
B, 
<number box="[1401,1413,1688,1709]" pageId="13" pageNumber="452" value="8.0">8</number>
C: ih); ventral margin of posterior lobe of surstylus strongly convex (
<figureCitation box="[858,926,1717,1738]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1938,1960]" captionTargetBox="[201,1347,206,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[185,1357,195,1913]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Male genitalia of Merodon kopensis sp. n., lateral view. A. epandrium; B. hypandrium; ab—aedeagal box; nnotch on theca to which is attached the aedeagal apodeme; ih—inner processes of the hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245533/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="452">Figs. 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[936,948,1717,1738]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1661,1683]" captionTargetBox="[222,1371,366,1643]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[203,1384,349,1655]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of Merodon neonanus sp. n. A – B. epandrium, lateral view; C. hypandrium, lateral view; D. distal end of aedeagus, ventral view; A—Greece; B—FRY of Macedonia; ab—aedeagal box; n—notch on theca to which is attached the aedeagal apodeme; ih—inner processes of the hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245535/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="452">8</figureCitation>
